fix(quant): ADX line uses proper Wilder RMA + yfinance MultiIndex hardening

Issues discovered during 5-year TOP100 backfill:

1. ADX runaway (observed: ADX=575 on 5y of 0050 data)
   `_wilder_smooth` was applied to the DX→ADX line, but that function
   implements Wilder's *running-sum* smoothing meant for TR/DM. It adds
   the raw value each bar instead of value/n, causing the smoothed
   output to grow unbounded over long histories.

   The DI calculation cancels out the missing 1/n factor because both
   numerator (smoothed DM) and denominator (smoothed TR) use the same
   smoother. ADX has no such cancellation — it needs proper averaging.

   Fix: introduce `_wilder_average` (the correct RMA used for the ADX
   line) and route the DX → ADX smoothing through it.

   Before: 0050 5y bars → ADX=575.19 (off-scale)
   After : 0050 5y bars → ADX=41.09  (correct trending_up signal)

2. yfinance MultiIndex columns
   yfinance >= 0.2.x returns MultiIndex columns where the level holding
   field names ("Open", "High", ...) can be 0 OR 1 depending on version
   and `group_by`. Previous code assumed level 0, producing duplicate
   columns and breaking float() conversion in upsert.

   Fix: detect which level actually contains OHLCV field names, then
   deduplicate columns post-rename. Backfill upsert also coerces
   anything pandas-shaped to a scalar before float() / int().

3. Lunar New Year false positives in data_integrity_checker
   TW market closes for up to 9 consecutive weekdays around Lunar
   New Year. Threshold raised from MAX_GAP_TRADING_DAYS=5 to 10.

Backfill report (local, taiwan_stock.db):
    universe = 94 curated symbols
    ok       = 92 (>= 1000 bars, ~5 trading years)
    thin     = 1  (00919 — newer ETF, 865 bars)
    failed   = 1  (2888  — delisted/merged)
    total    = ~115k DailyPrice rows

Verified locally:
    /api/v1/scanner/scan?bias=LONG → 9 LONG across 93 symbols, all
        with data_source="real", real RSI (32-90), real prices
    /api/v1/brief/today regime → trending_up, ADX=41.09,
        slope200=+0.34%/bar
    /api/v1/universe/active → 86 active / 8 inactive (liquidity floor)
    6 LONG signals persisted to edge_signals for walk-forward evaluation

Tests: 132/132 still green after all fixes.

New helper:
    scripts/persist_today_signals.py — one-shot CLI to seed edge_signals
    when the scheduler hasn't run yet.

